Section 1:
1 L.D. 1105
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 LABOR
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 724, L.D. 1105, “An Act Concerning
10 Displaced Civilian Federal Firefighters in Maine”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1407 in the first indented paragraph in the 3rd line (page
12 1, line 6 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "shipyard," the following: 'a'
13 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2.
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment is the majority report of the committee. The amendment removes the
1188 provision of the bill that requires municipalities, when filling an open position for a
1199 firefighter, to give priority consideration to civilian federal firefighters who have been
2200 displaced due to a reduction in force at or closure of a federal military installation. It retains
2211 the provision of the bill that requires the Department of Labor to establish and maintain a
2222 database of displaced civilian federal firefighters in Maine.
2233 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2244 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR0116(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
